The cost of inaction is mounting, and as a country, we need to act now and deliver deep cuts to emissions. | | | Peter,
This week**,** 98 million people in the U.S. were under ‘Code Red’ air quality alerts after hazardous smoke from over 400 Canadian wildfires drifted south, blanketing parts of the Northeast, Mid-Atlantic, Ohio Valley, and Midwest in a thick, orange haze. Overnight, New York City had the worst air quality of any major city on Earth**** —**** and amid the acrid smoke and ominous Mars-like skies, people in over 18 states got a devastating wake-up call: **The climate crisis is not coming. It is here now. And it impacts everyone, everywhere.** [**That’s why we’re asking you today to join us in calling on President Biden to use his executive power to declare a National Climate Emergency and meet this moment with the scope and urgency necessary. Sign our petition today — Tell Biden: Declare a National Climate Emergency**](https://an.workingfamilies.org/ss/c/P8Elou2Rvc0qoMPEUZrMXdJUvH8Ygu3R43gD0WUPlZ4hBOhRoKsHGyS29kY6YXzj7t6IHlUPjc4vbvzD_Fck2NUBnderSvclXU_snQNI9QZyCOo29ktS6u8yt615TWorxTygNRrbKCaYRcx3xqwWdba61HuswVMQOfQhs-oYXVxGxB6D5-rF_PezrDTrs1JMuEcPe-Te_dxP38lRInSZobkzjc7YgeQkGJH7nXNskdkfIR7-3vWwMDcsgqZfn35MrCZnikmPQCGNE1iBjXN90qubOxtu1EpR2eKKdS7p7obVRvFjoD8Fs1QKbrH04iUlJqL7XQRnWbTWzLnccuS5YX-YnsQTzjaRj8nUf2nJCbA/3ww/s9OUO7MMSjKiZIxVqwr6FQ/h0/Iq5zspoDaSHPMLY1seAd2p_1cuv6xrXQmCBjMWdbBPc). **[Sign the petition »](https://an.workingfamilies.org/ss/c/P8Elou2Rvc0qoMPEUZrMXdJUvH8Ygu3R43gD0WUPlZ4hBOhRoKsHGyS29kY6YXzj7t6IHlUPjc4vbvzD_Fck2NUBnderSvclXU_snQNI9QZyCOo29ktS6u8yt615TWorxTygNRrbKCaYRcx3xqwWdba61HuswVMQOfQhs-oYXVwl33aDQLCtZbsb3QS7pUNYOyZOxRjYFua45TOEBeQYOz0yeNqk_13nFy3WZuEKOHYHRYLohe4tOy_4SEZHOkKYoP_b_UdVMXIaq_EpSblfaNb-i0EdOxAX1haupOzWrfC1S47bNc0aNIof5V8oqFDUNgC5Cp7Sm4OCh6VNJTNOpTZ_zD8PT3i7GjHXFem4Y1w/3ww/s9OUO7MMSjKiZIxVqwr6FQ/h1/FLvezsmw9iSPgzc90DqN2EK_MeN6abvKBoymbm8IkVQ)** What people on the East Coast experienced this week is a version of what some of the rest of the country, and parts of the world, have already been dealing with for _years_. **On Pacific islands** , indigenous people are already bearing the brunt of tidal changes. In the **Global South** , Black and brown folks are already undergoing climate-forced migration. And on our very own **West Coast** , record-breaking heat and wildfires are already scorching homes and leaving low-income families with nowhere to go. **The weather extremes and climate disasters we are**** _all_****already living through make it clear that we’re out of time. This is an emergency. And we need to treat it as one.** We have already locked in a hotter future, but we still have a chance to prevent the most devastating outcomes and create a livable future for all. Declaring a National Climate Emergency would enable President Biden to unlock the tools and resources to tackle this crisis head on and safeguard our planet, including the ability to:
* Halt crude oil exports;
* Suspend offshore oil and gas drilling;
* Restrict international trade in fossil fuels;
* Order the construction of renewable energy systems in climate-vulnerable communities;
* And leverage Defense Production Act (DPA) funds to manufacture clean energy tech.1

The cost of inaction is mounting, and as a country, we need to act now and deliver deep cuts to emissions. [**Can you add your name to our petition to demand President Biden declare a National Climate Emergency and unlock the tools needed to steer us away from fossil-fueled climate catastrophe toward a just, livable future?**](https://an.workingfamilies.org/ss/c/P8Elou2Rvc0qoMPEUZrMXdJUvH8Ygu3R43gD0WUPlZ4hBOhRoKsHGyS29kY6YXzj7t6IHlUPjc4vbvzD_Fck2NUBnderSvclXU_snQNI9QZyCOo29ktS6u8yt615TWorxTygNRrbKCaYRcx3xqwWdba61HuswVMQOfQhs-oYXVwxw27LJbrI3E9xnooxHkFVjF87kzvrVcY_KLeTmdDjGOArutNSEVkSZYRPgFaaVAO9v8aGskGpOTNmJHEwaXbOSJ0uNJKsKwgPqv6J8EcMc2cxfqh17gQwpyNW1IzCFRjqhFVt9P1BL8m-B_pQfiVlnRI9n7naLh-C9zCFay6fpzyUOWa-bXIlVnCq-dS8y4M/3ww/s9OUO7MMSjKiZIxVqwr6FQ/h2/tKY_VNPpiQM-2LlH_llzzEtm2Y_Pu65JPZyCnL8aRcg) **[Sign the petition »](https://an.workingfamilies.org/ss/c/P8Elou2Rvc0qoMPEUZrMXdJUvH8Ygu3R43gD0WUPlZ4hBOhRoKsHGyS29kY6YXzj7t6IHlUPjc4vbvzD_Fck2NUBnderSvclXU_snQNI9QZyCOo29ktS6u8yt615TWorxTygNRrbKCaYRcx3xqwWdba61HuswVMQOfQhs-oYXVzHdi1RWMfEqWzkbLJnET1T2bWoRwSDAlTNDZvlYJ7a0TbRY-6Dsm5kRzG_nzp0cI9UTcgwaVXDqZSwaou359LpoeUzc5Lz7sfV0bC5iVENYfFtgv2tAHkbzooosGltQ-Or7tolbuT-WFHso9xOR9E0M2UkFP2JfQHIgvPILT1jcUGJLk6TwvYteJ6kennyngY/3ww/s9OUO7MMSjKiZIxVqwr6FQ/h3/fNFEI38p1sZyxmFV1IwQipoFoHIvXWeeoFqFQgCzZwU)** In solidarity, Working Families Party Source:
